[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T19:55:06+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google Pixel 8 and Pixel 8 Pro on pink and blue backgrounds showing home screens with mineral wallpaper\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BQTsgVeeGSIDhyhdOqzxL7IoGTk=/21x0:1980x1306/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561624/DSC05706.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ny1fzp\">Last month, it was discovered that an inactive piece of software that ships on all Google Pixel smartphones <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/15/24221151/google-pixel-showcase-software-spyware-palantir-iverify\">presented a potential security vulnerability</a> for device owners. The company quickly said it would remove \u201cShowcase.apk,\u201d which was created years ago \u201cfor Verizon in-store demo devices and is no longer being used.\u201d But on the off chance it were ever exploited, cybersecurity firm iVerify found that the software could make phones \u201caccessible to hackers and ripe for man-in-the-", "id": 1076769, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24235127/google-pixel-showcase-vulnerability-patch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google releases Pixel update to get rid of surveillance vulnerability", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T19:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of Castlevania: Dawn of Sorrow as part of the Castlevania Dominus Collection.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iZ2bs5dszDC_huWrRCvFRhvtRtE=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561565/DoSPS_ScreenShot01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Castlevania: Dawn of Sorrow.</em> | Image: Konami</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"p1lAqz\">For anyone looking to explore the best <em>Castlevania</em> has to offer, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/27/24229521/castlevania-dominus-collection-nintendo-switch-ds-trilogy\">the just-launched <em>Castlevania Dominus Collection</em></a> is pretty much a no-brainer. It includes a trilogy of games from the Nintendo DS era that show <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/6/19/15830788/koji-igarashi-bloodstained-castlevania-interview-e3-2017\">designer Koji Igarashi</a> arguably at the height of his powers: the experiences combine smooth, satisfying action with worlds th", "id": 1076770, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234889/castlevania-dominus-collection-review-switch-xbox-playstation-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The latest Castlevania collection is truly excellent", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T18:44:33+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of a touchscreen inside a vehicle, with text on the screen indicating a question has been asked of the AI assistant.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/S4CVK1M0f6HNfc1rd8IHXNKu1S4=/0x53:2691x1847/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561449/Large_17987_VolkswagenbringsChatGPTtoitsvehiclesviavoiceassist.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Volkswagen</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UbEdoW\">Volkswagen has <a href=\"https://media.vw.com/en-us/releases/1813\">announced</a> it\u2019s rolling out its improved in-car AI voice assistant, IDA, with both locally processed and cloud-based responses from ChatGPT and other models, starting on September 6th. The first cars getting the feature will be the 2025 Jetta and Jetta GLI and the 82kWh battery version of the 2024 ID.4, with other cars getting it later this year.</p>\n<p id=\"DkCNFD\">Drivers in cars that support ChatGPT will need to be subscribed to VW\u2019s Plus Speech with AI service to ", "id": 1076290, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234979/volkswagen-vw-ai-chatgpt-plus-speech-id-4-gti-golf-r-tiguan", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "New VWs will answer some of your questions with ChatGPT ", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T18:30:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Bitcoin symbol on a blue and orange polka dot background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4wlaR_3PGa5zCnFHsiUTxulHxdk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561423/STK087_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_bitcoin.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6gjh9B\">People are losing a lot more money to Bitcoin ATM scams. In <a href=\"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2024/09/new-ftc-data-shows-massive-increase-losses-bitcoin-atm-scams\">a report released on Tuesday</a>, the Federal Trade Commission said it found the amount of money lost to Bitcoin ATM scams increased nearly 10 times from 2020 to 2023 \u2014 going from $12 million to a whopping $114 million. Consumers have already lost $65 million to the ruse in the first half of 2024 alone.</p>\n<p id=\"zYRHJT\">Over the years, scams have evolved into different versions of pretty much the same thing", "id": 1076291, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234886/bitcoin-atm-scammers-65-million-stolen-ftc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bitcoin ATM scammers stole $65 million in first half of 2024", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T18:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google Pixel 9 on a pink and green background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kxdxsqm7IYAaMfVFFFplL_7r-3k=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561331/DSC08161.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Google Pixel 9</em>. | Photo: Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6IbuuJ\">Android 15 has officially arrived \u2014 <a href=\"https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2024/09/android-15-is-released-to-aosp.html\">for developers, at least</a>. Google\u2019s next-gen operating system is available in the Android Open Source Project, with support for Pixel phones due to roll out in the coming weeks. You\u2019ll have to wait a little longer if you have a compatible device from Samsung, Motorola, OnePlus, Nothing, or other brands, while Google describes the window for Android 15 coming to those phones as within the \u201ccoming months.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"JLmiey\">While Apple typically rolls out major changes tied directly to ea", "id": 1076292, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234730/android-15-availability-circle-to-search-earthquake-alerts", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Android 15 is out \u2014 but it\u2019s not ready for your phone yet ", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:29:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration depicting a featureless face against a pink, white, and blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/q84f9mdMxkyTYfQMKcmJIfUkYzU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561086/acastro_210512_1777_deepfake_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"C04PJHEGR9D-1725379322.892559-thread-list-Thread_1725380311.570319\">Clearview AI has been hit with its largest fine yet under Europe\u2019s General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) by a Dutch regulator. The Dutch Data Protection Authority, or Dutch DPA, <a href=\"https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl/en/current/dutch-dpa-imposes-a-fine-on-clearview-because-of-illegal-data-collection-for-facial-recognition\">announced a fine of 30.5 million euros</a>, or about $33.7 million.</p>\n<p id=\"r42nww\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23919134/kashmir-hill-your-face-belongs-to-us-clearview-ai-fac", "id": 1075460, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234879/dutch-regulator-gdpr-clearview-ai-fine", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Dutch regulator slaps Clearview AI with $33 million fine and threatens executive liability", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:26:46+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A woman trekking through the ruins of a city. The woman\u2019s image is overlaid with a HUD indicating that she\u2019s being surveilled. \" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LQa5HYx1jL8_1Ik_C9brgDSWotQ=/153x0:2391x1492/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561071/Screen_Shot_2024_09_03_at_11.16.46_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Neon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CLPO2M\">Director Asif Kapadia is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2016/2/28/11121774/amy-best-documentary-feature-academy-awards-2016\">best known for his documentaries</a> chronicling the lives of entertainment <a href=\"https://slate.com/culture/2011/08/senna-reviewed-a-riveting-formula-one-documentary-about-the-purity-of-sport.html\">icons</a> whose work left indelible marks on the worlds of music and sports. But his next feature looks like a nightmarish vision of a future that feels all too possible.</p>\n<p id=\"BAuAJR\">Though <em>2073, </em>Kapadia\u2019s new film,<em> </em>featur", "id": 1075461, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234865/neon-2073-trailer-asif-kapadia", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Neon\u2019s 2073 paints a bleak picture of the future in new trailer", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:23:25+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Digital photo collage of a statue of justice with too many arms.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_6R3Ids1mBT3q4fFbzdWqbMJZhI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561063/STK470_AI_LAW_CVIRGINIA_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>California lawmakers push to regulate artificial intelligence.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24233767/california-ai-regulation-news-stories\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1075462, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24233767/california-ai-regulation-news-stories", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All the news about SB 1047, California\u2019s bid to govern AI", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:16:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Artwork for Marvel vs. Capcom Fighting Collection: Arcade Classics, featuring a group of Marvel heroes and Capcom fighters.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fyyVBS6dTEOCjw_ClJKBPU8lLCs=/300x0:1920x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561047/Marvel_vs._Capcom_Fighting_Collection_Arcade_Classics___Key_Art.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Capcom</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ny9LWs\">Capcom called and said Xbox can come along for the ride, too. The publisher has announced that it will release its two upcoming fighting game collections \u2014 <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180976/i-wanna-take-you-for-a-ride\"><em>Marvel vs. Capcom Fighting Collection: Arcade Classics</em></a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/27/24229594/capcoms-digging-up-all-the-old-classics\"><em>Capcom Fighting Collection 2</em></a> \u2014 on Xbox in 2025.</p>\n<p id=\"bIq4Fn\">Capcom announced the two games earlier this year for PlayStat", "id": 1075463, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234863/marvel-vs-capcom-fighting-collection-xbox-release-2025", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Capcom\u2019s two upcoming fighting game collections are heading to Xbox, too", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:15:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Concord illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f-j0NE23AXbrE2cTbkUHDb4J6Qg=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561045/ad3527b123d0c8dfcca5d4968a6dcf126e37a68dd290ef85.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Sony</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"I5qd6X\">Sony is taking <em>Concord, </em>its latest PlayStation game, offline on September 6th, following poor sales of the game. The first-person hero shooter launched exclusively on PS5 and PC on August 23rd, but <a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/concord-is-estimated-to-have-sold-only-25000-units-heres-why-analysts-think-its-failing?utm_source=twitter\">estimates have put sales</a> at under 25,000. <em>Concord </em>also only managed to hit an all-time peak of 697 players on Steam, lower than the launch peak of <em>The Lord of the Rings: Gollum \u2014 </em>widely regarded as the worst game of 2023.</p>\n<p id=\"MGymYT\">\u201cWe have decided to take the game offline beginni", "id": 1075464, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234909/sony-concord-ps5-shutdown-poor-sales-launch-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony is taking Concord offline on September 6th after disastrous launch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:13:32+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration featuring the Tesla wordmark logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IPMCiexk7r53TsAuxQ07bJh_lfE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73561037/acastro_180430_1777_tesla_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bXxK2N\">The news that Tesla will likely reveal its long-awaited, much-debated autonomous robotaxi at the Warner Bros. movie studio in Los Angeles underscores how much ground the company needs to cover in order to catch up to its rivals in the self-driving space. It also inadvertently provides a ready-made metaphor for the types of Hollywood trickery Elon Musk and Co. will no doubt need to employ in order to convince their supporters that Tesla\u2019s driverless technology is really ready this time. </p>\n<p id=\"LhVm9O\">Over the weekend, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-08-30/tesla-plans-robotaxi-reveal-at-california-", "id": 1075465, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234785/tesla-robotaxi-event-warner-bros-mapping-data-musk", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tesla will need some Hollywood magic for its robotaxi reveal", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A bare piece of blue shiny processor stands balanced on one corner\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0rQ8aiIbll1guOpRqquT4-wOBtw=/42x0:1931x1259/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560980/intel_lunar_lake_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A graphical representation of Intel\u2019s Lunar Lake chip.</em> | Image: Intel</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3Ab4Lr\">Do good things come to laptop buyers who wait? Today, <a href=\"https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/newsroom/news/power-efficient-core-ultra-200v-series-mobile.html\">Intel is revealing</a> its first nine answers to Qualcomm\u2019s Snapdragon X Elite and AMD\u2019s Strix Point laptop chips \u2014 and the company claims the new Core Ultra 200V lineup, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/3/24169115/intel-lunar-lake-architecture-platform-feature-reveal\">formerly known as Lunar Lake</a>, can meet or beat them in almost every way.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"Rw0Ro", "id": 1075467, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24233957/intel-lunar-lake-core-ultra-200v-launch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Intel reveals first Lunar Lake laptop CPUs: everything you need to know", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Copilot Plus PCs\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9OOml0uhkBDm5Nxdx21Q9vlQozM=/149x0:1771x1081/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560978/Copilot_PC_Hero.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ACblsX\">Intel says that Microsoft\u2019s new Windows AI features will start arriving on some of its laptops in November. AMD has already launched laptops that are capable of meeting Microsoft\u2019s Copilot Plus PC hardware requirements for Windows AI features, but the features have so far only been available on new Qualcomm-powered devices.</p>\n<p id=\"EhgzkC\">Intel is announcing new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24233957/intel-lunar-lake-core-ultra-200v-launch\">Intel Core Ultra 200V processors</a> today, codenamed Lunar Lake, which will start getting Copilot Plus PC features later this year. \u201cAll designs featuring Intel Core Ultra 200V series processors and running the latest ", "id": 1075466, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234687/microsoft-co-pilot-plus-pcs-intel-features-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s Copilot AI features are coming to new Intel laptops in November", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T15:22:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Xbox logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/d4J_8iPWJR8E8oafNzIPQwkuYO0=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560925/STK048_XBOX_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xfRY7n\">Earlier this year Apple <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/25/24050430/apple-app-store-game-streaming\">started opening up</a> its App Store to game streaming services like Xbox Cloud Gaming and GeForce Now, freeing them from being restricted to web apps on the iPhone and iPad. Despite multiple changes to Apple\u2019s App Store guidelines this year, Microsoft and Nvidia have still not published native cloud gaming apps for iOS, and Microsoft is now detailing exactly why.</p>\n<p id=\"1YKeui\">Microsoft already said earlier this year that Apple\u2019s cloud changes <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24073666/microsoft-gaming-phil-spencer-interview-ps5-switch-games\">don\u2019t go \u201cfar e", "id": 1074928, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234777/microsoft-apple-cloud-gaming-app-store-changes-xbox-cma", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u00a0and Apple are arguing over cloud gaming apps again", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T14:55:22+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of a woman typing on a keyboard, her face replaced with lines of code.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-jTyQH6IH4w6JhJ1S2tbo_K0lZg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560841/STK149_AI_Chatbot_K_Radtke.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"sdIUyz\">The organization behind National Novel Writing Month (NaNoWriMo) is being slammed online after it claimed that opposing the use of AI writing tools is \u201cclassist and ableist.\u201d On Saturday, <a href=\"https://nanowrimo.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/29933455931412-What-is-NaNoWriMo-s-position-on-Artificial-Intelligence-AI?ref=404media.co\">NaNoWriMo published its stance on the technology</a>, announcing that it doesn\u2019t explicitly support or condemn any approach to writing.</p>\n<p id=\"P32BlU\">\u201cWe believe that to categorically condemn AI would be to ignore classist and ableist issues surrounding the use of the technolo", "id": 1074929, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234811/nanowrimo-ai-stance-classist-ableist-criticism", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NaNoWriMo is in disarray after organizers defend AI writing tools", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T14:33:27+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pudQBEnmA__BMZHqCJ7DwSZ3jls=/0x0:799x533/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560798/53153261075_07bf3ef157_c.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The IFA tech show in Berlin, Germany is one of the biggest home appliance shows in the world. It\u2019s also a showcase for smartphones, computers, gaming, audio, home entertainment, and smart home.</em> | Image: IFA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap p-large-text\" id=\"zXeFyO\">I\u2019m a sucker for the smart kitchen. Build me a kitchen that can tell me what to cook, when to cook, how to cook it, and do the boring bits for me, then clean it all up afterward, and I\u2019ll be a happy tech reviewer. For years, this has seemed totally out of reach. Appliance makers have stuck Wi-Fi chips in everything, but have barely done anything to make those appliances smart. Unless all your appliances are from the same brand, nothing works together in the smart kitch", "id": 1074478, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24233534/ifa-tech-show-smart-kitchen-smart-appliances", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "I\u2019m heading to Berlin to seek the solution to the smart kitchen\u00a0  ", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T14:25:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Teal semitruck, head on view, on road in vast open field.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/el_xoVjmZp8r8LL5Wkgez4LtudM=/0x0:4085x2723/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560789/_59A8888_Original_file.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Volvo FH Electric commercial truck.</em> | Image: Volvo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QRG58J\">Volvo\u2019s commercial trucking division is launching <a href=\"https://www.volvogroup.com/en/news-and-media/news/2024/sep/breakthrough--volvo-to-launch-electric-truck-with-600-km-range.html\">a next-generation long-range version</a> of its flagship electric semitruck, due out in the second half of 2025, with twice the battery range of the previous one.</p>\n<p id=\"MmM2UE\">The new FH Electric truck can travel 600km, or about 373 miles, on a single charge. The current model <a href=\"https://www.volvotrucks.com/en-en/trucks/electric/volvo-fh-electric.html\">goes 300km</a>, or about 186 miles, in comparison, wh", "id": 1074479, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234736/volvo-long-range-fh-electric-semi-truck-2025", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Volvo\u2019s next electric semitruck goes 373 miles on a single charge", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T14:19:01+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Structure International Consumer Electronics Fair (IFA)\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XMPUfIQDLhTOEriqYRb354qZsnQ=/0x0:8256x5504/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560778/1634145688.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Sebastian Gollnow / picture alliance via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>Here\u2019s everything being announced from Europe\u2019s biggest tech show.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24231736/ifa-2024-news-products-updates-highlights-berlin\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1074480, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24231736/ifa-2024-news-products-updates-highlights-berlin", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "IFA 2024: all the news from the big Berlin tech show", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T14:03:23+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Bang &amp;amp; Olufsen\u2019s new Beoplay H100 wireless headphones in the sunset apricot colorway.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xm71qUbb8-wtUN8ykJaEhu5-ynI=/0x0:2500x1667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560751/BO_H100_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Bang &amp; Olufsen Beoplay H100 are available in three different colorways, including sunset apricot.</em> | Image: Bang &amp; Olufsen</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vvbPfe\">Bang &amp; Olufsen has announced its new <a href=\"https://bang-olufsen.presscloud.com/digitalshowroom/#/pressreleases/973123827730752\">$1,549 Beoplay H100 headphones</a>, which are debuting with an even steeper price tag than its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/8/31/21409031/bang-olufsen-beoplay-h95-noise-canceling-headphones-announced\">H95, which were introduced four years ago</a> and which now cost $999. The company is justifying that pricing with a focus on premium materials, improved no", "id": 1074481, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234719/bang-olufsen-wireless-headphones-beoplay-h100-anc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bang & Olufsen\u2019s new $1,500 headphones combine luxury and repairability", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T13:45:56+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the iPhone 14 laying on a glass surface.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Msj1DhQa1gBTKhU_27yVrO137Ec=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560684/226270_IPHONE_14_REGULAR_PHO_akrales_0736.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The iPhone SE 4 may look a lot like the iPhone 14.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XqYQcV\">The fourth-generation iPhone SE might be getting an OLED display, a new rumor bubbling up from its supply chain suggests. The company has started ordering OLED displays from both BOE and LG Display to outfit the phone with, <a href=\"https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Supply-Chain/Japan-no-longer-iPhone-display-supplier-as-Apple-ends-LCD-use\">according to <em>Nikkei Asia</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"yM9UAl\">The possibility that Apple was switching its cheapest phone away from LCD tech has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/6/23628019/apple-iphon", "id": 1074482, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234749/apple-iphone-se-4th-generation-oled-display-rumor-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s next iPhone SE might get an OLED upgrade", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Three backpacks are shown in white, black, and deep purple from front, side, and back with the back panel unzipped to show how the bag stores a hydration pouch and hose.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/csgoMMMsFEIkbP2gAjAWcgDBjf8=/0x50:2100x1450/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560558/peak_design_outdoor_family.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Outdoor Backpack is available in 45L and 25L models.</em> | Image: Peak Design / Composite The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QzNt1K\">San Francisco-based Peak Design \u2014 maker of one of our <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2016/10/11/13240828/peak-design-everyday-backpack-review-not-an-ad\">all-time</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/7/26/16031314/verge-editors-choice-peak-design-everyday-backpack\">favorite</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23809717/backpack-bag-sling-favorite-laptop-phone-tech-fanny-pack\">backpacks</a> \u2014 is back with its first new bag lineup ", "id": 1074081, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24232208/peak-design-outdoor-backpacks-slings-price-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Peak Design\u2019s Outdoor bags are ready for your next adventure", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Four new EcoFlow devices are shown as renders resting on solid columns like Roman gods.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ybCk0YiGeOOI1hxBLRy8SjboOx8=/0x103:896x700/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560421/KV_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>From left to right: the River 3, the Rapid power bank, the Delta 3, and the Power Kit v2.</em> | Image: EcoFlow</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"lC9W0h\">EcoFlow just launched four new battery products designed to power everything from your home appliances in the event of a blackout to your Qi2-compatible phone to RVs. </p>\n<p id=\"hD7C28\">Going from most powerful to least, there\u2019s the second-generation Power Kit to power your off-grid vanlife fantasies, the midrange Delta 3 and compact River 3 solar generators, and the Rapid Qi2 wireless power banks for phones that can also charge your laptop in a pinch.</p>\n  <figure class=\"e-image\">\n        \n      <cite>Image: EcoFlow</cite>\n      <f", "id": 1073649, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234116/ecoflow-power-kit-river-3-delta-3-rapid-specs-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "EcoFlow launches four new batteries for phones, homes, and RVs", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T11:50:37+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Canva logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9S3qBOeIP4DF-nTAAB2x_fGZce8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73560406/STK263_CANVA_D.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Existing subscribers Canva teams subscribers are being moved to a new, more expensive pricing model.</em> | The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cRoXuA\">The price of some Canva subscriptions are set to skyrocket next year following the company\u2019s aggressive rollout of generative AI features. Global customers for Canva Teams \u2014 a business-orientated subscription that supports adding multiple users \u2014 can expect prices to increase by just over 300 percent in some instances. Canva says the increase is justified due to the \u201cexpanded product experience\u201d and value that generative AI tools have added to the platform.</p>\n<p id=\"5uiHYG\">In the US, some <a href=\"https://x.com/wlsndrs/status/1829521548233122098\">Canva Teams users are re", "id": 1073650, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234698/canva-price-increase-300-percent-ai-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Canva says its AI features are worth the 300 percent price increase", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-03T07:00:00+00:00", "description": 